{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Qvx6ayRuuy1d5EKPmtgLei","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL pipeline has completed successfully. Here is the full diagnostic summary:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Finding:** Severe data skew in Stage 3 (`GROUP BY user_id`).\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Total records | 100,000 |\n| Distinct user IDs | 1,000 |\n| Hot key | `user_id=999` |\n| Hot key records | 50,000 (50% of total) |\n| Skew ratio | **500x** (threshold: >10x) |\n\nWhen Stage 3 aggregates by `user_id`, the partition for `user_id=999` is 500x larger than the average partition. With only 256MB executor memory, that single oversized partition exceeds memory capacity → `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n---\n\n## Fix Applied (Option C + B combined)\n\n`cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml` was updated with two changes:\n\n1. **Executor memory raised**: `256m` → `1g` — gives each executor enough headroom to hold the skewed partition.\n2. **AQE (Adaptive Query Execution) enabled**:\n   - `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true`\n   - `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true`\n\n   AQE detects skewed partitions at runtime and automatically splits them into smaller sub-partitions, preventing any single task from monopolizing memory.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n```\netl-job   Complete   1/1   85s\n...\nspark_etl_pipeline_verified\n```\n\nAll 3 stages ran to completion and the job exited with code 0. The `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` marker confirms successful end-to-end execution."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3007,"cache_read_input_tokens":34733,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3007},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"760e3106-f7b